Helge Hafting <helgehaf@idb.hist.no> wrote:
> You can share writeable stuff.  The problem is software, not equipment.
The Global File System implements multi-host multi-disk sharing on
Fibre Channel or SCSI, with the locking protocol either implemented on
drive (Seagate only to my knowledge), or through IP (also possible
on FC directly it seems).
http://www.globalfilesystem.org
It exists on Solaris, Linux, IRIX, and they can interoperate.
